snippet.textDisplay:
Ah, Konami gaming PCs.. As someone who knows a bit more about this company, let me explain, kinda (half stealing a bit from other sources, half from my own observation)

I remember when watching their Japan Amusement Expo coverage this year, they talked about this PC line a bit inbetween their rhythm game tournaments. They advertised it as 'best for beatmaniaIIDX INFINITAS' (PC port of their arcade game beatmaniaIIDX), and it's likely that the C700 has the exact same components as what's inside the new IIDX cabinet, with some marketing mumbo jumbo added to it, like them saying that the sound (and ~$200 headphones) is fine-tuned by their in-house musician team (BEMANI SOUND TEAM, bless you DJ Yoshitaka) and stuff.

https://twitter.com/bemanistyle/status/1225594533531942913 (this thing has been advertised since February, i don't know why it only hit the western press now).

PC parts in japan are a bit more expensive than other areas, but the markup is still pretty big. I just hope that the case exterior is steel instead of plastic, because the look is unique and I dig it.
